{
  "local_port": 37650,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which earphones are better under 2000?",
  "response": "Choosing the right earphones under \u20b92,000 depends on your specific needs, such as whether you prefer wired or wireless, prioritize sound quality, battery life, comfort, or additional features like noise cancellation. Below are some top-rated options across different categories that offer excellent performance within your budget:\n\n### **1. Wireless Earphones**\n\n**a. Realme Buds Air 3 Neo**\n- **Price:** ~\u20b91,799\n- **Features:**\n  - True wireless design with Bluetooth 5.2\n  - Up to 18 hours total playback with charging case\n  - Low latency mode for gaming\n  - Multiple EQ modes for customized sound\n- **Pros:**\n  - Good battery life\n  - Reliable connectivity\n  - Comfortable fit\n- **Cons:**\n  - Average noise isolation\n\n**b. OnePlus Buds Z2**\n- **Price:** ~\u20b92,499 (Often available with discounts close to \u20b92,000)\n- **Features:**\n  - Active Noise Cancellation (ANC)\n  - Bluetooth 5.2\n  - 30 hours total playback with ANC off\n  - IP55 water and sweat resistance\n- **Pros:**\n  - Effective ANC for the price\n  - Good sound quality\n  - Fast charging\n- **Cons:**\n  - Slightly above \u20b92,000, but discounts often bring it within budget\n\n### **2. True Wireless Earbuds**\n\n**a. Redmi AirDots 3 Pro**\n- **Price:** ~\u20b91,999\n- **Features:**\n  - Bluetooth 5.3\n  - AptX support for better sound quality\n  - Touch controls\n  - Up to 28 hours total playback (with case)\n- **Pros:**\n  - Excellent battery life\n  - Crisp sound quality\n  - Lightweight design\n- **Cons:**\n  - Limited ANC features\n\n**b. pTron Tangent Pro TWS**\n- **Price:** ~\u20b91,499\n- **Features:**\n  - Bluetooth 5.0\n  - Low latency mode\n  - LED indicator\n  - IPX4 water resistance\n- **Pros:**\n  - Budget-friendly\n  - Decent sound quality\n  - Comfortable fit\n- **Cons:**\n  - Basic features compared to higher-priced models\n\n### **3. Wired Earphones**\n\n**a. Sony MDR-EX155AP**\n- **Price:** ~\u20b91,299\n- **Features:**\n  - 9mm neodymium drivers\n  - Noise-isolating design\n  - Built-in microphone and remote\n  - Tangle-free flat cable\n- **Pros:**\n  - Reliable sound quality\n  - Comfortable for long use\n  - Durable build\n- **Cons:**\n  - Lacks advanced features like ANC\n\n**b. Panasonic ErgoFit RP-TCM125**\n- **Price:** ~\u20b9499\n- **Features:**\n  - Ergonomic design with multiple ear tip sizes\n  - 12mm driver units\n  - In-line remote and mic\n- **Pros:**\n  - Extremely affordable\n  - Good sound for the price\n  - Comfortable and secure fit\n- **Cons:**\n  - Basic features, no noise cancellation\n\n### **4. In-Ear Monitors (IEMs)**\n\n**a. CCA C12**\n- **Price:** ~\u20b91,500\n- **Features:**\n  - 40mm dynamic drivers\n  - Detachable MMCX cables\n  - In-line remote and mic\n- **Pros:**\n  - Great sound quality for the price\n  - Durable with detachable cables\n  - Good bass response\n- **Cons:**\n  - Wired design limits mobility\n\n**b. KZ ZS10 Pro**\n- **Price:** ~\u20b92,499 (Often available with discounts around \u20b92,000)\n- **Features:**\n  - Hybrid driver setup (1 dynamic + 4 balanced armature)\n  - Detachable cables\n  - In-line controls\n- **Pros:**\n  - Excellent sound clarity and detail\n  - Robust build quality\n  - Customizable fit with various ear tips\n- **Cons:**\n    - Slightly above budget but offers high performance\n\n### **Key Considerations When Choosing Earphones:**\n\n1. **Usage:** Determine if you need them for casual listening, workouts, gaming, or professional use.\n2. **Wired vs. Wireless:** Wireless offers more freedom of movement, while wired often provides better sound quality for the price.\n3. **Battery Life:** Especially important for wireless models; check both usage and standby times.\n4. **Comfort:** Look for ergonomic designs and various ear tip sizes to ensure a secure fit.\n5. **Sound Quality:** Consider the driver size and overall sound profile (bass-heavy, balanced, etc.).\n6. **Additional Features:** Features like ANC, water resistance, and fast charging can enhance your experience.\n\n### **Final Recommendations:**\n\n- **Best Overall Wireless:** *Realme Buds Air 3 Neo* offers a balanced mix of features and performance within the \u20b92,000 budget.\n- **Best True Wireless:** *Redmi AirDots 3 Pro* provides excellent battery life and sound quality for true wireless enthusiasts.\n- **Best Wired Earphones:** *Sony MDR-EX155AP* is a reliable choice with good sound and build quality.\n- **Best IEM:** *CCA C12* delivers impressive sound quality with a durable design, ideal for audiophiles on a budget.\n\nBefore making a purchase, it's advisable to check the latest prices and user reviews, as promotions and availability can change frequently. Additionally, consider purchasing from reputable retailers to ensure you receive an authentic product with a valid warranty.",
